{{!-- Inner body of the sitewide "If you loved this, here's how to
     support" CTA. Lives in its own partial so partials/membership-cta
     can include it from BOTH the signed-in-free-Subscriber branch
     AND the anonymous-visitor branch without duplicating markup.

     Voice: reader-first. Reframed from "essays like this are made
     possible by readers" (third-person editorial pitch) to "if this
     piece was worth your time, here's what to do about it" — a
     direct response to the moment a reader has just finished an
     essay they enjoyed. --}}
<section class="membership-cta">
    <div class="cta-inner">
        <p class="eyebrow">Loved this essay?</p>
        <h2><em>Help us write the next one.</em></h2>
        <p>
            Mere Orthodoxy is reader-supported. If this piece was worth your time, become a Member — you'll get the print journal mailed to your door, the full archive, and the satisfaction of helping us commission the next essay you'll want to read.
        </p>
        <div class="cta-buttons">
            <div class="cta-stack">
                <a href="/membership/" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Become a Member</a>
                <p class="btn-tagline">Get the journal and support Mere Orthodoxy</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p class="cta-secondary">
            Not ready to commit? <a href="/membership/">See all plans &rarr;</a>
        </p>
    </div>
</section>
